CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1967, pg. 17, reads: "African Look - Because this group's costumes represented those worn by natives of Africa, judges selected them among the many prize winners at the AKA 'Ajoyo' From left: Al Stewart, Nadine Frye, Kay Fitts, Michael Oyeyipo, Nan Currington, Judith Nelson, Marsha Demamame, and Shelton Zvoma.  The latter two are Africans attending school here."
TitMainTitle: Al Stewart, Nadine Frye, Kay Fitts, Michael Oyeyipo, Nan Moone Currington, Judith Nelson, Marsha Demamame, and Shelton Zvoma wearing African costumes, in the Flying Carpet for Alpha Kappa Alpha "Ajoyo"
